ICE DRAGON

Ice Dragons share the power tier of Fire Dragons but breathe frost instead
of flame and are immune to cold rather than heat.  Like all young dragons,
they are MDC beings of staggering physical capability with innate magic and
psionic powers.  They are drawn to cold wilderness regions and polar zones.

ATTRIBUTES (approximate ranges):
  IQ: 15-30  ME: 13-28  MA: 11-26  PS: 25-50 (Supernatural)
  PP: 9-24   PE: 24-44  PB: 6-21   Spd: 14-34

DAMAGE POOL:
  MDC: 4d6 x10 + 60 (approx 100-300 MDC)
  HP: PE + 2d6 (inner life force)

SPECIAL ABILITIES:
  - MDC body: immune to SDC/HP weapons
  - Supernatural Physical Strength and Endurance
  - Ice/frost breath weapon
  - Complete immunity to cold and frost
  - Natural flight
  - Nightvision 300 ft
  - Telemechanics: instinctively understand any machine
  - Sense Rifts and ley lines
  - Starting PPE: approximately 200+

PENALTIES:
  - Not OCC eligible
  - Dragon-sized: cannot enter most buildings
  - Hunted by multiple factions
  - Cannot use standard equipment

OCC ELIGIBLE: No.
ALIGNMENT: Any.

